snippet.title: Aquaman Spoiler Review
snippet.description:
Aquaman directed by James Wan and starring Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman, Patrick Wilson, Willem Dafoe, Temeura Morrison and Dolph Lundgren swims out to sea this holiday season. The film professes to be an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas. The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime—one that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be…a king.

Kristian Harloff, Perri Nemiroff, Denniz Tzeng and Dorian Parks are here to give you their SPOILER filled review of the film. They look at the action, direction, special effects, visuals and storylines of the movie. They let you know what worked for them in the film and what did not. They also let you know if this is part of the new direction for DC. Let us know what you thought of the movie in the Comments section below.
